title: Diggs-ing Deep
report:
Welcome back to the Jart Report after a week ten filled with more low scoring performances across the board and not much sweating. With The Family getting back on track scoring wise for Roto purposes, we are excited to dive into what was an interesting week as matchups start to carry more and more weight.

Prediction: United Nations by 11.7

Reality: Team ACL Tear by 12.58

“Incredible resiliency from my boys. Good riddance Matty Ice you suck!” - Lopey

“So many bad decisions from me this year” - MW

Jart’s Mailbag

Who are your first round picks if you did a redraft right now?

I considered breaking this up into two different drafts, one for so far this season, and one for the rest of the season. But instead, we’re going to produce a composite here.

  1. Jonathan Taylor, Dmichs
  2. Najee Harris, NN
  3. Austin Ekeler, JL
  4. Cooper Kupp, NN
  5. Ezekiel Elliott, Folbe
  6. Joe Mixon, JL
  7. James Conner, Bank
  8. Alvin Kamara, Jase
  9. D’Andre Swift, Jart
  10. Nick Chubb, CJ
  11. Dalvin Cook, Aross
  12. Tyreek Hill, Jart

What is your realistic prediction for JL the rest of the season?

It was not going to be very favorable had Deebo not dropped 27 and gotten JL to 9-1 last night. Left on the schedule is Folbe, Jart, CJ, Jason. I think the most likely result there is 2-2, leaving JL at 11-3. Considering Alex will probably play the lowest PF team every week the rest of the season, they’ll both be 11-3, but JL will have the tiebreaker by like 600 points. So he’ll have the 1 seed and a first round bye. In the semi-finals he’d face the winner of the 4/5 matchup, which as of today is Folbe-CJ. I think his most likely opponent in this round in NN though, and I think NN just has too much firepower for JL. So I think semi-final exit is the most likely result, but a trip to the finals would not surprise me. He still has the best odds to win it all in my mind given his first round bye and Aross winning last night.

Who was the worst draft pick?

Excluding players who have missed time because of injuries since only Dr. Banooni can see those coming, I think the answer has to be Allen Robinson. It was certainly a surprise that he has been so horrendous, but he’s the #64 WR in fantasy this season and has yet to score 10 points in a game. He’s borderline droppable, which is certainly not what one would have expected, including myself who was pretty high on him this season. If we count injured players, it’s probably Saquon Barkley.

Best draft pick by round?

  1. Najee Harris, NN. Ekeler may have slightly better numbers so far, but Najee went a couple picks later, so he gets the slight edge.
  2. Jonathan Taylor, Dmichs. Also self-explanatory.
  3. James Robinson, MW. Not because he’s been amazing, but because the 3rd rd of our draft was atrocious.
  4. D’Andre Swift, Jart. Also not a great round for the league, but Swift is a top-10 back pretty much every week.
  5. Darrell Henderson, Jase. That guy is just nice, even with last night’s poor showing. Honorable mention here to Brandon Aiyuk, NN.
  6. Ja’Marr Chase, Jart. I stopped reading the rest of the round, it’s Chase.
  7. Tom Brady, Bank. This one was real close between Brady and Hurts, but Brady has been slightly better. Shoutout Robby Anderson, Jason.
  8. Deebo Samuel, JL. Also stopped reading the rest for this one.
  9. James Conner, Bank. Somehow he’s super good. I’m still a little confused by it.
  10. Marquise Brown, Dmichs. I love it for my nephew Hollywood, and he’d probably be WR1 on the year if he could catch.
  11. Dallas Goedert, Dmichs. Another not great round for the league, and it was between him and McKissic. I like Goedert to be a top option the rest of the year though at TE.
  12. Bills D/ST, CJ. They too nice.
  13. Chuba Hubbard, Nooni. Not much utility nowadays, but he was a solid starting RB for weeks with McCaffrey out (which will probably happen again soon).
  14. Tyler Bass, Aross. While both Elijah Moore and Rhamondre Stevenson may be coming on now, Tyler Bass has been the consistent #1 kicker all year.

How Dead am I?

Good question Bank. I think we can all agree the Edmonds and Arwin injuries help your team, so Trees is really the only loss (Ridley wasn’t even that good when he played). Devonta and Hunter have both been solid WR2s, so I don’t think you’re dead at all. I could see this being one of your best weeks yet.

40 Yard Dash Finish Predictions?

  1. CJ. That guy’s first in everything!
  2. Nooni. I’m not convinced about this one since he just sits in a goal all soccer game, but maybe he can move.
  3. Jonah. MW kinda remembers his being a nice sprinter, that’s good enough for me.
  4. Folbe. Crop top aerodynamics baby.
  5. Aross. Was higher pre-ACL.
  6. Jart. None of you have seen me in years. So I’ll put myself in the middle and play it safe.
  7. Dmichs. Never met the guy, don’t trust him. But if the cops are on him, he’s moving.
  8. Merrick. If it was a Peloton 40 yard dash we’d have him at one.
  9. Jason. Guy’s dusting NN and then hitting the griddy at the end.
  10. Bank. I don’t know what it is, but I don’t see him moving.
  11. Brad. His lack of self-confidence does him in.
  12. NN. I trust him when he says he’s last.

Who do I play?

Jason I don’t know if this was a question for your matchup for next week or for the mailbag. So I put it in both. After doing some research, I have discovered that you play Dmichs.

On To Week Ten!

This Week’s Matchups:

Team Ross vs United Nations: The most notable thing to me when I looked at this matchup was that both of Alex’s TEs are on bye. Both of these teams have struggled mightily to score points, but Aross has been winning while MW has been losing. Lamar and Dalvin form a formidable duo, but this writer before Herbert-McCaffrey. We find it hard to trust Gaskin, AJB, Allen, and Mike Davis on any given week. While both of these teams have been inconsistent at best and this one may not top 100 points on either side, we expect a bit of an upset this week, and have United Nations by 8.6.

Aross: “Don’t know who I play but good win”

MW: “Just worried about my team not the opponent”

I Got a Half Chubb vs Mike Williams WR1: Pat Mahomes is back, but will the rest of the team catch up? We’re not sold on it. The loss of Cordarelle Patterson has forced Juice Landry back into the lineup, and Jeff Wilson Jr’s role should continue to grow in San Fran as he returns from injury, hurting Elijah Mitchell’s stock. BMW and Cooks are too inconsistent, and Kittle disappeared after the first drive last night. The team can compete, but we don’t see it this week. For CJ, Rodgers should be back to normal this week with a full week of practice, and gets to feast upon a weak Minnesota secondary. Chubb has the best matchup in history, RIP DMONT is back, Hopkins and Thielen both get nice ones, and Andrews and Diontae have proven somewhat matchup proof. This one shouldn’t be close, and we like I Got a Half Chubb by 25.6.

Brad: “Going to destroy CJ so I make his IG story”

CJ: “Lol I got brad this week”

GRIDDY GANG vs CalAmari Cooper: Jase, I’m sorry. I wish this season had gone differently for you. If Kamara plays, then there is an outside shot with the Kamara-Jefferson-McLaurin trio. If he doesn’t though Jason has about zero shot. For Dmichs, Dak-Taylor-Hollywood-Kelce is proving a tough combo to beat, and should continue their high level of play this week. Dmichs has certainly evolved into a top-tier contender, and we see no signs of him slowing down this week. We like CalAmari Cooper by 32.4.

Jase: “Who do I play”

Dmichs: “Gg Jason you win”

Real Brothers vs Pray for Ridley: This is probably the best team Bank has fielded yet (if you think I’m kidding, I’m not). Gaining two bellcows via injury, Conner and Dillon lead a team with solid WRs and Tom Brady. If Damien Harris can’t play, Rhamondre Stevenson is a major problem as well. For Jart, the return of Saquon looms large, while Mark Ingram may be in a phenomenal position if Kamara can’t play this week. That RB2 spot will be one to watch this week, while the QB and TE/WR/FLEX spots are locked in with Hurts-Adams-Hill-Chase-Pitts. The talent is certainly higher on Jart’s side, but the production has not yet been there consistently to trust it week in week out. Bellcows are the safest thing in fantasy, so we like Pray for Ridley by 5.6.

Jart: “I got a lot of respect for Bank. Injuries have really helped him out. Conner+Dillon a scary duo. Boys are gonna have to bring it this week if we want to have a chance. Can’t be scoring 70 points again this season or else I’m in trouble”

Bank: “Jart is still in trouble”

Team Horses vs Team ACL Tear: One team underperforming with its talent, the other probably overperforming. For JL, the health of Kyler continues to be a key question, while Ekeler-Mixon-Lamb-Samuel has proven a formidable core. For Folbe, WR remains a major question mark as Beta Metcalf, Waddle, and Higgins have yet to prove they are reliable options. Perhaps Chris Carson slides into the FLEX upon his return, joining Zeke and Fournette in what is a solid RB stable. This team is led by Josh Allen, and it should be his play that puts this team on top this week. We like Team Horses by 7.6.

Folbe: “Jonah’s team is bad just in time for our matchup. How nice of him”

JL: “I hope my boys play as well as Folbe dances next week”

NN vs Nooni: This is probably the most lopsided matchup of the season, although Stafford and Kupp on bye does help some (although it also puts Hendoggy on bye). Jakobi is scoring tuddies now though, and Nooni has likely the worst team this league has seen. We like NN by 37.6.

NN: “Who tf is Nooni gonna start at RB1 or RB2”

Nooni: “Don’t know my upcoming matchup don’t care. Just want over 100 pts”

Best Player at Each Position

QB: Pat Mahomes, Brad

RB: Nick Chubb, CJ

WR: Stefon Diggs, NN (bad luck to pick one of my guys)

TE: Kyle Pitts, Jart (good luck to pick one of my guys)

D/ST: Patriots D/ST, JL (classic)

K: Fat Randy, FA

Family Award

This week’s award goes to Jason. Idk why, but I found a way to make it happen.
